physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Town Church in Rangoon, Burma. There is a fence around the church. The entrance is made of three archways. There is an attached tower structure on the right of the church. Behind the church, there are smaller roofed buildings on the left and right of the photograph.There is an area of empty land in front of the church at the forefront of the photograph. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Town Church, Rangoon
subject_terms_2: Photographs Thomson, J. (John), 1837-1921 Rangoon (Burma) Church buildings Cathedrals
